<!-- FAQ Section -->
<section class="faq">
    <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="faq-container">
        <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question">
                <span>How do I create an event?</span>
                <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
                <p>Simply log in to your account, click "Create Event" in the navigation menu, fill out the event details including title, description, date, location, and maximum attendees, then publish. Your event will be visible to all users immediately.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question">
                <span>Is there a cost to use Event Hub?</span>
                <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
                <p>Event Hub is completely free to use! You can create unlimited events, manage attendees, and participate in events at no cost. We believe in making event management accessible to everyone.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question">
                <span>Can I edit an event after publishing?</span>
                <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
                <p>Yes! As the event organizer, you can edit any details of your event at any time before it starts. Simply go to the event details page and click the "Edit" button. Changes are reflected immediately.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question">
                <span>How do I RSVP to an event?</span>
                <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
                <p>Find the event you want to attend, view its details, and click the "RSVP" button. You can choose your attendance status (Attending, Maybe, or Not Attending) and add guest information if needed.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question">
                <span>Can I leave reviews for events?</span>
                <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
                <p>Absolutely! After attending an event, you can leave a review with a rating and comments. These reviews help other users find great events and help organizers improve their events.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question">
                <span>What happens if an event reaches capacity?</span>
                <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
                <p>When an event reaches maximum capacity, you'll be offered the option to join the waiting list. If a spot opens up due to cancellations, you'll be notified and can confirm your attendance.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

